Bexar County ISD School Finance Map

This is a map for use with the RvSA Story, using an altered moonlight theme from Mapbox.

How Schools Get Their Money In Bexar County

This chart is important because it illustrates the local burden placed on schools under a property tax school financing system. Wealthier districts still retain an overall net benefit because they gave a greater pile of money in the end. Under a property tax scenario, the schools with more local financing end up with greater pools of money.
